---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms and Conditions — Spam Detector"
  description="Terms of service for Spam Detector. Read about acceptable use, disclaimers, and limitations of liability before using our free phishing and spam detection tool."
  canonical="https://spamdetector.app/terms"
>
  <main id="main-content" class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 flex-1">

    <div class="mb-8">
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] text-[#888] dark:text-[#666] uppercase tracking-widest mb-1.5">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-[28px] font-semibold text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed] tracking-[-0.7px] text-pretty">Terms and Conditions</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] text-[#888] dark:text-[#666]">Effective date: <time datetime="2025-01-01">January 1, 2025</time></p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-[#111111] rounded-xl border border-[#ebebeb] dark:border-[#2e2e2e]
                shadow-[0_1px_1px_rgba(0,0,0,0.02),0_2px_2px_rgba(0,0,0,0.04)]
                divide-y divide-[#ebebeb] dark:divide-[#2e2e2e]">

      {[
        {
          id: 'agreement',
          title: '1. Acceptance of Terms',
          body: `By accessing or using Spam Detector at spamdetector.app ("Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Service. We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time; continued use following any modification constitutes your acceptance of the updated terms.`,
        },
        {
          id: 'description',
          title: '2. Description of Service',
          body: `Spam Detector is a free, AI-powered tool that analyses text, URLs, images, and other content to estimate the likelihood that it constitutes spam, phishing, or malicious content. Results are provided as a spam risk score (0–100), a classification, and a natural-language explanation. The Service is intended for informational and educational purposes.`,
        },
        {
          id: 'acceptable-use',
          title: '3. Acceptable Use',
          body: null,
        },
        {
          id: 'disclaimer',
          title: '4. Disclaimer of Warranties',
          body: `THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, ACCURACY, OR NON-INFRINGEMENT.\n\nSpam risk scores and classifications are probabilistic estimates generated by an AI model. We do not guarantee that all spam or phishing content will be detected, nor that legitimate content will never be flagged. Always exercise your own judgement and verify results independently before acting on them.`,
        },
        {
          id: 'liability',
          title: '5. Limitation of Liability',
          body: `TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, SPAM DETECTOR AND ITS OPERATORS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, REVENUE, DATA, OR GOODWILL, ARISING FROM OR RELATED TO YOUR USE OF THE SERVICE — INCLUDING ANY RELIANCE ON ANALYSIS RESULTS THAT PROVE TO BE INACCURATE.\n\nOur total liability for any claim arising from or related to the Service shall not exceed the amount you paid to use the Service (which is zero for the free tier).`,
        },
        {
          id: 'third-party',
          title: '6. Third-Party Services',
          body: `The Service uses the OpenAI API to generate analysis results. OpenAI is an independent third party, and content you submit is processed under OpenAI's terms of service and privacy policy. We are not responsible for OpenAI's data handling, availability, or accuracy of outputs. Use of the Service constitutes acceptance of OpenAI's applicable policies.`,
        },
        {
          id: 'ip',
          title: '7. Intellectual Property',
          body: `All original code, design, and content on this website is owned by or licensed to Spam Detector. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works from the site's proprietary materials without prior written permission.\n\nContent you submit for analysis remains yours. By submitting content, you grant us a limited, royalty-free, non-exclusive licence to process that content solely for the purpose of providing the analysis service.`,
        },
        {
          id: 'termination',
          title: '8. Termination',
          body: `We reserve the right to restrict, suspend, or terminate access to the Service at any time and for any reason, including but not limited to violations of these terms, abuse of the API, or unusual traffic patterns that indicate automated or malicious use, without notice or liability.`,
        },
        {
          id: 'governing-law',
          title: '9. Governing Law',
          body: `These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with applicable laws, without regard to conflict-of-law principles. Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of the Service shall be resolved through good-faith negotiation before any formal legal proceedings.`,
        },
        {
          id: 'contact',
          title: '10. Contact',
          body: `Questions about these Terms should be directed to legal@spamdetector.app or via our Contact page. We will respond to written inquiries within a reasonable timeframe.`,
        },
      ].map(section => (
        <section id={section.id} class="px-6 py-5">
          <h2 class="text-[14px] font-semibold text-[#171717] dark:text-[#ededed] tracking-[-0.2px] mb-3">{section.title}</h2>
          {section.id === 'acceptable-use' ? (
            <div class="text-[13px] text-[#4d4d4d] dark:text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed space-y-2">
              <p>You agree to use the Service only for lawful purposes. You must not:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 pl-1">
                <li>Submit content that you do not have the right to share or analyse.</li>
                <li>Use the Service to facilitate, plan, or execute spam, phishing, or cyberattacks against others.</li>
                <li>Attempt to reverse-engineer, scrape, or automate requests to the Service in a manner that places excessive load on our infrastructure.</li>
                <li>Use the Service to test or refine phishing campaigns, spam software, or social engineering attacks.</li>
                <li>Circumvent or attempt to circumvent any rate limits or access controls.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>We reserve the right to block access from IP addresses or networks that violate these guidelines.</p>
            </div>
          ) : (
            <div class="text-[13px] text-[#4d4d4d] dark:text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-line">{section.body}</div>
          )}
        </section>
      ))}

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
